The '''311th Human Systems Wing''' ('''311 HSW''') is a [[wing (air force unit)|wing]] of the [[United States Air Force]] based out of [[Brooks City-Base]] in [[San Antonio]], [[Texas]].
==Mission==

Enhance and sustain [[human]] performance for dominant air and space power.

==History==


===Operations===


===Previous designations===

*Medical Resource Laboratory (1918 <U+2013> 1922)
*School of Aviation Medicine (1922 <U+2013> 1959)
*Aerospace Medical Center (1959 <U+2013> 1961)
*Aerospace Medical Division (1961 <U+2013> 1987)
*Human Systems Division (1987 <U+2013> 1990)
*Armstrong Laboratory (1990 <U+2013> 1997)
*Human Effectiveness Directorate (1997 <U+2013> 1998)
*311th Human Systems Wing (1998 <U+2013> Present)

